# hermes-operator chart — exploratory placeholder (TBA)
#
# Not committed to yet. The recommended way to run a Hermes "team" today is
# an ArgoCD ApplicationSet over ../hermes-agent/ (roster as data, this chart
# as the template) — see ../../docs/teams.md.
#
# A dedicated operator (Agent / AgentTeam CRDs, developed in a separate,
# external repo) would only be worth building if that ApplicationSet's
# templating-only model falls short in practice, e.g.:
#   - a single object reporting team-wide status
#     (kubectl get agentteam <name> -> "3/4 members healthy")
#   - admission-time validation of team-level invariants
#     (e.g. "every member shares one DISCORD_HOME_CHANNEL")
#   - active reconciliation / state machines (e.g. role reassignment on
#     member failure)
#
# If/when that happens, this directory would host the chart that installs
# the operator (CRDs + controller + RBAC) — the controller itself would live
# in its own repo.
#
# See ../../README.md#roadmap. Nothing here yet.
